        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="section-icon"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i></div>
          <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-container">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">How do I check my <%=data.title%> status?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>
                You can check your <%=data.title%> application status by visiting the official website <%=data.important_links[0].title%> and clicking on "Beneficiary Status." Enter your Aadhaar number or  registration number to view your status.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">What if my land records are not updated?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>
                You should first approach your local revenue office to update your land records. Once updated, you can apply for the  scheme with the revised documents.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">I haven't received my installment. What should I do?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>
                Check your application status online first. Common reasons for delayed payments include pending verification, bank account issues, or incorrect details. You can also contact your local agriculture office or call the <%= data.title %> helpline at <%= data.helpline_numbers.
toll_free %>.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">Can I update my bank account details?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>
                Yes, you can update your bank account details by visiting the nearest Common Service Centre (CSC) or by logging into the <%= data.title %> portal using your registered mobile number.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">Are tenant farmers eligible for <%=data.title%>?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>
                No, tenant farmers who do not own the land they cultivate are not eligible for scheme benefits. The scheme is designed for landholding farmers only.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
